President Obama announced his intent to nominate Joseph B. Donovan as a member of the Board of Directors of the National Institute of Building Sciences. Donovan is currently Senior Vice President at Beacon Capital Partners and has extensive experience in real estate investment and facilities management. 

Bruce R. Sievers was nominated as a member of the National Council on the Humanities. He is a visiting scholar and lecturer at Stanford University and has a background in philanthropy and civil society. 

The President also announced his intent to appoint Miaohong Hsiangju Liu as a member of the President’s Advisory Council on Faith-Based and Neighborhood Partnerships. Liu has been involved in humanitarian projects and has represented Buddhist organizations at the United Nations. 

Barbara Williams-Skinner was appointed as a member of the President’s Advisory Council on Faith-Based and Neighborhood Partnerships. She is the President of Skinner Leadership Institute and has a background in leadership development and advocacy.